cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses P2P content delivery systems and proposes a new system for incentivizing peers to participate in such systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with decentralized content delivery. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel Proof of Delivery mechanism and discusses guarding against liars and Sybil attacks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new system for structuring incentives in P2P content delivery systems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of financial incentives to attract peers in P2P content delivery systems.
